<DOC><DOCNO> AP890210-0187 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-02-10-89 2218EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Burma-Drugs     02-10 0110</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Burma-Drugs,0113</SECOND><HEAD>Thousands Arrested on Drug Offenses in Burma</HEAD><DATELINE>RANGOON, Burma (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The military and police arrested more than3,700 people and seized more than 3,000 pounds of opium in drugraids last year, a state-owned newspaper said Friday.   The total worth of the seizures, which also included 854 poundsof marijuana and 414 pounds of high-grade heroin, is $11.2 million,the Working People's Daily said.   The raids on both jungle and urban hideouts produced 3,718arrests and netted 3,032 pounds of opium, the report said. Nodetails were given on the status of those arrested.   Opium, a major product in Burma, can be refined to make heroin.</TEXT></DOC>